{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01503/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01503"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:15:03"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tilt, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A waitress brings a customer two plates full of food."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01503","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01503"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1/c0881b16-d859-4c6d-9d37-d3919052f195","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:32:26.630Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds’s breakfast order is very English, featuring tea, scones, sausages, and Welsh rarebit (“rabbit,” a cheesy toast which, contrary to its name, is likely not a dish originating in Wales). This sense of Englishness is only amplified by the prominent display of the Victoria Hotel emblem on the plate, a reference to the long-reigning monarch who still sat on the throne at the time of the hotel’s establishment in 1897. While the film references Alma’s foreign origins only obliquely, this framing of Reynolds as the consummate English gentleman against Alma as a non-English member of the service class suggests that Reynolds feels a degree of power over her in their initial encounter.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01503/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:845.485401459854,395.92335766423366,296.60583941605853,174.05474452554733"}}}]}]}]}